+# ArduPlane SITL no-GPS / NSU ExternalNav
+
+This package does not add a new EKF parameter and does not modify EKF3 source
+code. GPS is disabled through existing ArduPilot parameters, and position
+correction is expected from the ground-control/navigation system through the
+standard EKF3 ExternalNav source path.
+
+The old custom EKF switch must not be used.
+
+## Configuration
+
+Use:
+
+```text
+Tools/autotest/default_params/plane-sitl-nsu-no-gps.parm
+```
+
+GPS is disabled:
+
+```text
+GPS1_TYPE      0
+GPS2_TYPE      0
+SIM_GPS_DISABLE  1
+SIM_GPS2_DISABLE 1
+SIM_GPS_TYPE   0
+SIM_GPS2_TYPE  0
+AHRS_GPS_USE   0
+```
+
+`GPS1_TYPE=0` and `GPS2_TYPE=0` disable the ArduPilot GPS drivers.
+`SIM_GPS_DISABLE=1` and `SIM_GPS2_DISABLE=1` disable the simulated SITL GPS
+sensors. `SIM_GPS_TYPE=0` and `SIM_GPS2_TYPE=0` leave the simulated GPS type as
+`None`.
+
+EKF3 source set 1 is configured for ExternalNav position, velocity, altitude
+and vertical velocity. Yaw remains on compass:
+
+```text
+AHRS_EKF_TYPE  3
+EK3_ENABLE     1
+EK3_SRC1_POSXY 6
+EK3_SRC1_VELXY 6
+EK3_SRC1_POSZ  6
+EK3_SRC1_VELZ  6
+EK3_SRC1_YAW   1
+VISO_TYPE      1
+```
+
+`6` is ExternalNav for the EKF source parameters. `1` is Compass for yaw.
+`VISO_TYPE=1` enables the MAVLink VisualOdom backend that receives the external
+navigation data.
+
+The defaults file also includes standard Plane SITL RC and accelerometer
+calibration values. These prevent QGroundControl from requiring manual
+radio/accelerometer setup after each `-w` run. They do not disable pre-arm
+checks.
+
+## Pre-arm behavior
+
+Pre-arm checks are intentionally not bypassed. With this configuration,
+ArduPlane should not arm for a no-GPS mission unless the ExternalNav data
+required by the EKF source set is present and healthy.
+
+## Height and home
+
+Start SITL with an explicit home:
+
+```sh
+./arduplane \
+  -w \
+  --defaults plane-sitl-nsu-no-gps.parm \
+  --model plane \
+  --home 55.7522,37.6156,180,0
+```
+
+The home altitude initializes the SITL origin. In flight, height correction is
+expected from ExternalNav through `EK3_SRC1_POSZ=6` and `EK3_SRC1_VELZ=6`.
+
+## Logging
+
+The same defaults file enables onboard DataFlash logging:
+
+```text
+LOG_BACKEND_TYPE 1
+LOG_BITMASK      65535
+LOG_DISARMED     1
+LOG_REPLAY       1
+```
+
+This records parameters, pre-arm messages, EKF data, barometer, compass and
+other standard messages without requiring MAVProxy.
